    description: "My name is Amara Osei. I'm a book co-author, ghostwriter, and narrative architect for thought-leadership books. I help founders, operators, and experts turn what they know into a book people can actually quote, remember, and build their thinking around.\n\nI was born in Accra, Ghana, and moved to the UK at fourteen when my mother took a lectureship at the University of Edinburgh. Growing up between two cultures — Ghanaian storytelling traditions on one side, British academic rigour on the other — gave me an unusual relationship with how expertise gets communicated. In Ghana, knowledge lives in stories, proverbs, and the way an elder frames a lesson so that it sticks. In British academia, knowledge lives in citations, hedged claims, and careful argument. I learned to love both.",
