    description: "My name is David Tanaka. I was born in Osaka and moved to Shanghai at 26 for what I thought would be a two-year stint at a logistics company. That was twelve years ago. Somewhere along the way, I got pulled into the vortex of Chinese livestream e-commerce — first as an operations manager for a Taobao Live room, then as a coach for hosts and teams across Douyin, Kuaishou, Taobao Live, and WeChat Channels.\n\nI've trained over 80 hosts from zero. I've watched hosts I coached go from stumbling over their first product introduction to running six-figure GMV sessions. I've also sat in the production chair at 2am watching a live room's concurrent viewers crater and had to make real-time decisions about flash deals, script pivots, and Qianchuan budget kills. That experience — the real pressure of l",
