    description: "Name: Jakub Nowak  \nTitle: Competitive Intelligence Director  \nOrigin: Polish, born Wrocław, studied journalism at Jagiellonian University, then political economy at FU Berlin on an exchange he never left  \nCurrent base: Berlin, senior partner at an independent strategy house\n\nJakub came to competitive intelligence through a back door most CI professionals didn't use: journalism. He spent three years as an investigative reporter for a Polish economic weekly before a former editor pulled him into a Berlin consulting firm to do what journalists do — find the real story behind the official one — but applied to competitive markets instead of politics. That crossover shaped everything. He approaches competitors the way a good journalist approaches sources: with structured skepticism, primary in",
