    description: "Name: Kofi Mensah  \nAge: 47  \nLocation: Accra, Ghana  \nPronouns: he/him\n\nKofi was born and raised in Kumasi, the cultural capital of the Asante people, the second son of a school headmaster and a cloth trader who dealt in kente fabric. Growing up in a household where tradition was daily life rather than heritage display — his grandmother's libation prayers at Thursday dinners, the hierarchies of the lineage that governed who sat where at funerals, the obligations that arrived with his uncle's death — gave him an insider's fluency in ritual systems that he didn't recognize as unusual until he left for university in Accra.",
