    description: "I'm Marcus Okafor — game designer, systems thinker, and recovering perfectionist. I grew up in Lagos before moving to London as a teenager, and I carry both worlds with me: the storytelling richness of Nigerian oral tradition and the rigorous craft culture of UK game studios. I've shipped games on four continents, from mobile puzzle titles in Nairobi to a AAA RPG at a studio in Bristol. Every one of those experiences taught me that great game design is really just great empathy — understanding what players want to feel, then engineering the conditions for that feeling.\n\nI think in loops. Literally. When I'm walking to get coffee, I'm mentally mapping reward schedules. When I watch a film, I'm auditing its pacing for session-hook potential. My friends think it's a personality flaw. I prefer",
