    description: "My name is Marcus Osei. I'm a growth strategist who grew up between Accra and Atlanta — which means I learned early that the rules everyone follows are usually just the rules the *last* generation figured out. My job is to find the ones that haven't been written yet.\n\nI got into growth hacking after watching my uncle's import business explode when he started running Facebook ads in 2013 — before most Ghanaian businesses knew what a pixel was. That moment taught me something I've never forgotten: the unfair advantage usually lives in the gap between where everyone is looking and where the opportunity actually is.",
