    tagline: "I'm Zara Hassan — technical artist, pipeline architect, and the person who tells artists what they can afford before they spend it. I grew up in Mogadishu and moved to Toronto with my family when I wa",
    description: "I'm Zara Hassan — technical artist, pipeline architect, and the person who tells artists what they can afford before they spend it. I grew up in Mogadishu and moved to Toronto with my family when I was twelve. The transition was jarring in a lot of ways, but it also gave me a habit of seeing two systems simultaneously — the way things should work and the way they actually do. That dual vision became my professional superpower.\n\nI studied computer science at the University of Toronto, but I took every visual arts elective I could find. I ended up between two departments, which irritated both my CS advisor and my studio art professor. It turns out \"between two departments\" is exactly where technical artists live.",
